        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 18 at 1:16PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 115 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Cardiff, or near Gardendale, moving east at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Sayre, Ketona Lakes, Pinson, Palmerdale, Cardiff, Wattsville,
Chalkville, Shops of Grand River, Bald Rock, Watson, New Castle,
Grayson Valley, Margaret, Gardendale, Camp Winnataska, Center Point,
Fultondale, Morris, Harrisburg, and Branchville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
